text: Mitch Cahalane (born 5 May 1989) is an Australian rugby league player who most recently played for Halifax in the Kingstone Press Championship. He plays as a Prop. Cahalane has played for the Mount Pritchard Mounties in the NSW Cup and was previously in the system of the Penrith Panthers. ==References== ==External links== *Halifax profile Category:1989 births Category:Living people Category:Rugby league props Category:Halifax R.L.F.C. players Category:Mount Pritchard Mounties players
